                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#00" n="#">Fol. 82rb: Note on commissioning of the writing. </locus>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 82rb: በአሠርቱ፡ ወሰለስቱ፡ ብር፡ ተጽሕፈት፡ ወዘአጽሐፋ፡ በወርቁ፡ አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ ሕይወት፡ ትኩኖ፡ መርሐ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ አቡነ፡ ዘ[በ]ሰማያት፡ ወለአመትከ፡ ፍሬ፡ ማርያም፡፡</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 82rb: [This book] was made written for 30 Bərr. The one who commissioned it with his money is ˀabunä Gäbrä Ḥəywät, so that it might be for him a guide to the kingdom of heaven … </q>
                           <p part="N"/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title of the work ግንዘት is written twice, once in yellow ink and the other in pen, on fol.1r.&#xD;
- The scribe used compressed script on fol. 2ra-vb, 82ra-vb.&#xD;
- Corrections written interlineally: fols. 6ra, 17ra, 32va.&#xD;
- Miner notes: fols. 6v, 7v, 8r, 37r, 59r.&#xD;
- A crude note mentioning some names on fol. 85v.&#xD;
- Notes in the upper margins referring to the content or the section of the text: fols. 19r, 24v, 34v, 38r, 39v, 42v, 44v, 45v, 47v, 53r, 56r, 62v, 71v, 77r.&#xD;
- A tämälläs-sign of a peculiar shape (ጭ) indicating the place where the omission written in the margin, belongs, on fol. 21vb l. 5.&#xD;
- Ethiopic numbers written in the upper margins in pen:  fols. 53v, 54r-v.&#xD;
- Space for rubricated names left unfilled in the supplication formula: fol. 84r-v.</item>
                     </list>
